    "intro": "Interpretation moves from what the text says to what it means — tracing Isaiah's argument in its original context of the Babylonian threat, its place in the canonical unfolding of redemption, and its theological freight for a church that reads these promises in Christ. Where Hebrew vocabulary changes the shade of the English, a brief note follows as supplement.",
